  "title": "Preschool L2 English Teacher (Central & South)",
  "description": "<p><strong>🌟Well-established Preschool expanding and looking for driven teachers to grow with the company.🏫</strong><br /><br /><strong>Gross Salary:</strong> Up to $5100 (Basic: Up to $4500)<br /><strong>Benefits:</strong> AWS & Performance Bonuses & Medical<br /><strong>Working Days:</strong> Monday - Friday<br /><strong>Positive and encouraging environment with structured career progression</strong><br /><br /><br /><strong>Job Scope:</strong></p><ul><li>Plan and conduct developmentally appropriate English lessons in accordance with the centre’s curriculum</li><li>Create a positive, engaging, and inclusive classroom environment</li><li>Support children’s learning and development across cognitive, social, emotional, and physical domains</li><li>Prepare teaching materials and organise daily classroom activities</li><li>Observe, document, and report on children’s learning progress</li><li>Communicate professionally with parents and provide regular updates</li><li>Ensure adherence to safety, hygiene, and ECDA regulatory standards</li><li>Work collaboratively with colleagues to support centre operations and events</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>ECDA-recognised L2 teaching certification</strong></li><li><strong>LON - L2</strong></li><li><strong>Diploma in Early Childhood Care & Education (or equivalent)</strong></li><li>Passionate about working with young children and supporting their development</li><li>Strong communication and classroom management skills</li><li>Responsible, patient, and able to work well in a team</li><li>Familiarity with ECDA and centre licensing requirements is an advantage</li></ul><p>Interested applicants, please send your latest updated resume to felix@talentsatwork.sg or apply on the job ad. Applicants will be contacted to speak more on the opportunity.<br /></p><p>Talents@Work Pte Ltd (21C0501)<br />Felix Tan Chin Kuang (R25158946)</p>",
